import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['normal'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    data_to_plot = data[['actual', 'normal']]
    melted_data = data_to_plot.melt(var_name='Temperature Type', value_name='Temperature')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='Temperature Type', y='Temperature', data=melted_data)
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Temperature Type', labels=['Actual', 'Normal'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the trend of actual temperature over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='actual', y='forecast', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between actual temperature and forecasted temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Forecasted Temperature')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['record'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='record', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['record'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['record'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Record Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of record temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
